      "message": "I\u0027m not sure if it\u0027s reasonable to name the metric with \"sampled\" prefix. The purger randomly samples invocations that has expired test results, and then reports\n- the total number of the randomly selected invocations into the count metric.\n- the purge delay of the randomly selected invocations into the delay metric.\n\nI would not name the delay metric with \"sampled\" prefix. Both metrics report the status/health/extra_information of the invocations that purger performed its work against. It doesn\u0027t matter how the purger selected the reported invocations.",
